Yamakawa Manufacturing Corp ofAmerica said it began construction of a 17 mln dlrsmanufacturing plant in Portland, Tenn.    The plant will produce metal parts for automobilemanufacturers, including Nissan Motor Manufacturing Corp USA.    Long-term plans call for the addition of stampingcapabilities and pressed plastic parts to its product line.    Assembly operations are expected to begin in October 1987.The plant is being built to employ 150 people.    Yamakawa is a wholly-owned subsidiary of YamakawaIndustrial Co Ltd of Japan. Reuter&#3;